      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "GCI-based discretization error < 5% for primary QoI; asymptotic convergence demonstrated across minimum three mesh levels.",
      "rationale": "Three-level mesh refinement study yields GCI of 3.1% for NIH. Apparent order 1.94 confirms asymptotic range. Richardson extrapolation applied. Discretization uncertainty propagated to final hemolysis prediction bounds. Achieved level 3 exceeds MRL 2 requirement of level 2."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test conditions",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Experimental test conditions documented and traceable; boundary conditions in simulation matched to test conditions within stated uncertainty.",
      "rationale": "FDA benchmark experimental conditions fully documented in Hariharan et al. (2011). Inlet flow rates, rotational speeds, and fluid properties (bovine blood, 37°C) replicated in simulation. Boundary condition uncertainty estimated at ±2% for flow rate, ±0.5% for rotational speed."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Output comparison",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Quantitative comparison metric defined; simulation predictions compared against experimental measurements with uncertainty bounds; agreement within acceptance threshold at all validation points.",
      "rationale": "Normalized index of hemolysis (NIH) used as primary comparison metric. Predictions compared at 5 operating points. Mean relative error 8.3%, maximum 14.1%. However, formal uncertainty quantification of experimental measurements was not obtained from the original FDA dataset custodians; only nominal experimental values used in the comparison. Statistical validation metric (E_val) computed without experimental uncertainty contribution, which underestimates the validation interval. Agreement appears satisfactory on a point-estimate basis, but the absence of experimental uncertainty propagation means the achieved level of output comparison rigor does not meet the required level 2 threshold for this MRL 2 assessment."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the quantities of interest",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "QoIs directly linked to clinical endpoint; mapping from model output to device performance metric documented.",
      "rationale": "NIH and relative hemolysis index RH directly correspond to clinical hemolysis risk. Mapping from CFD shear stress field through power-law hemolysis model (Giersiepen et al.) to NIH is documented and peer-reviewed. QoI relevance confirmed by regulatory precedent in 510(k) submissions."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the validation activities to the COU",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Validation geometry, operating conditions, and fluid properties sufficiently representative of COU; extrapolation distance documented.",
      "rationale": "Validation performed on FDA generic centrifugal pump — same device class and operating envelope as COU. Fluid properties (bovine blood as surrogate for human blood) introduce minor extrapolation, documented with sensitivity analysis showing <4% impact on NIH predictions. Geometric similarity confirmed for impeller diameter and volute design."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Numerical solver error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 1,
